external_knowledge:
- "Average passing yards" refers to the total passing yards divided by the number of games played;
- "Difference" in this context means the team's average passing yards minus the player's average passing yards;
- The player with the highest difference is the one who contributes the most to the team's passing game relative to their own performance.

- The "top-performing team" is determined by the highest average score and the most games won;
- The "best player" is the one with the highest average passing yards and passing touchdowns;
- The player must be from the top-ranked team.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT game_id) AS game_count
FROM game_stats
WHERE pass_yds_off > 1000 AND rush_yds_off > 500;

external_knowledge:
- "passing yards" refers to the total distance the ball is thrown during a game;
- "season" is a specific period during which a series of games are played;
- "team" represents a group of players competing in the games.
